headline_main: And Now, the Dream of a Harris-Buttigieg Ticket
headline_print_headline: The Dream of a Harris-Buttigieg Ticket

abstract: Kamala Harris dominated the night from beginning to end. Pete Buttigieg also got good reviews.
snippet: Kamala Harris dominated the night from beginning to end. Pete Buttigieg also got good reviews.
lead_paragraph: When the candidates took the stage in Miami on Thursday for the second night of Democratic primary debates, former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Senator Bernie Sanders were the stars. By the time they walked off, all eyes were on Senator Kamala Harris.

headline_main: Who Won the Democratic Debate, Night 2? Experts Weigh In

abstract: Already the subject of detailed proposals from several Democratic presidential candidates, the issue of voting rights is now an integral part of the 2020 election.
snippet: Already the subject of detailed proposals from several Democratic presidential candidates, the issue of voting rights is now an integral part of the 2020 election.
lead_paragraph: When the Supreme Court ruled 5-4 on Thursday that federal judges had no power to stop partisan gerrymandering, it brought to a crushing end decades-old questions about the court’s willingness or ability to rein in voting maps drawn to blatantly benefit one party.

abstract: With one exchange about race, the senator began to take aim at Joe Biden’s tenuous hold on his front-runner status in the Democratic presidential field.
snippet: With one exchange about race, the senator began to take aim at Joe Biden’s tenuous hold on his front-runner status in the Democratic presidential field.
lead_paragraph: This was the moment Joseph R. Biden Jr. had to know would be coming. He did not seem entirely prepared.
